[Deal "E:AJT96.A62.AQ.T52 Q72.953.8764.AJ7 K854.KQ84.T52.KQ 3.JT7.KJ93.98643"]
[Auction "E"]
1S pass 2NT pass 3NT pass 4S pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{WEST's 2NT response is Jacoby - a game forcing ♠ raise.

EAST's 3NT bid shows extra strength, a 5-card trump suit and no singleton/void. This is

definitely NOT a suggestion to play Notrump - the trump suit is already agreed as ♠s.

WEST cannot make any positive move, so she bids 4♠ which EAST passes.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
{Baker Bidpractice/Set9 3}
[Dealer "S"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Student "S"]
[Deal "S:AJT762.KT.AJ6.J4 98.7643.732.AKT5 KQ53.QJ5.KQ.9732 4.A982.T9854.Q86"]
[Auction "S"]
1S pass 2NT pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{Following NORTH's Jacoby 2NT, SOUTH bids 3♠. This is stronger than 4♠ and

shows a 6-card suit.

NORTH has already bid the full strength of his hand so he signs off with 4♠ which SOUTH passes.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]

