[Student "S"]
[Deal "W:AQJ743.KQJ5.J3.7 8.T982.AKT874.43 K9652.A76.Q5.KQ8 T.43.962.AJT9652"]
[Auction "W"]
1S pass 2NT pass 3C pass 3H pass 4S pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{The 3♣ bid shows a singleton / void in ♣s.

EAST doesn't have much strength above what she has already shown, but she takes advantage

of the bidding level to make a control-showing 3

♥

bid.

WEST is concerned about the

♦

suit with a worthless doubleton,

and he knows that EAST doesn't have first-round control. He bids 4♠ and EAST passes.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]

